    [upload("2024/06/Glutinous-rice-600x450-1.jpg")],
    "GLUTINOUS RICE",
    "<div class=\"row vc_row wpb_row vc_inner vc_row-fluid\">\n<div class=\"wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"vc_column-inner\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row vc_row wpb_row vc_inner vc_row-fluid\">\n<div class=\"wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"vc_column-inner\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"wpb_single_image wpb_content_element vc_align_center\">\n<figure class=\"wpb_wrapper vc_figure\">\n<div class=\"vc_single_image-wrapper   vc_box_border_grey\">\n<div class=\"row vc_row wpb_row vc_inner vc_row-fluid\">\n<div class=\"wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"vc_column-inner\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n\n<strong>1 – Thai White Glutinous Rice</strong>\n\nThai White glutinous rice is a type of rice grown mainly in Southeast and East Asia and the eastern parts of South Asia, which has opaque grains, very low amylose content, and is especially sticky when cooked. It is widely consumed across Asia. It is called glutinous in the sense of being glue-like or sticky, While often called “sticky rice”, it differs from non-glutinous strains of japonica rice which also become sticky to some degree when cooked.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"vc_column-inner\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"wpb_single_image wpb_content_element vc_align_center\">\n<figure class=\"wpb_wrapper vc_figure\">\n<div class=\"vc_single_image-wrapper   vc_box_border_grey\"><img class=\"vc_single_image-img \" title=\"Glutinous rice\" src=\"/uploads/2024/06/Glutinous-rice-600x450-1.jpg\" alt=\"Glutinous rice\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></div></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"vc_empty_space\"></div>\n<div class=\"row vc_row wpb_row vc_inner vc_row-fluid\">\n<div class=\"wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"vc_column-inner\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n\n<strong>2 – Thai Black Glutinous Rice</strong>\n\nBlack glutinous rice (or Black sticky rice) is a nutty whole grain widely consumed in many of Southeast and East Asia and the eastern parts of South Asia .A naturally sweet, dark rice (dark purple more than black) that has both fiber and loads of antioxidants.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"vc_empty_space\"><img class=\"vc_single_image-img \" title=\"Thai black glutinous rice\" src=\"/uploads/2024/06/Thai-black-glutinous-rice-600x383-1.jpg\" alt=\"Thai black glutinous rice\" width=\"600\" height=\"383\" /></div>\n</div></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\nGlutinous rice, despite its name, is free of gluten. It’s a distinct variety known for its sticky, chewy texture when cooked, making it a culinary gem in many Asian cuisines. Its naturally sweet flavor and cohesive texture set it apart from other rice varieties. Our glutinous rice is meticulously cultivated and processed to ensure the highest quality, offering a delightful experience to culinary enthusiasts and chefs alike.\n<ul>\n \t<li><strong>Packaging Options:</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li><strong>Bulk Packaging:</strong> Available in bulk quantities ranging from 25 kg to 50 kg sacks, designed for commercial use and large-scale culinary operations.</li>\n \t<li><strong>Retail Packaging:</strong> Consumer-friendly options include smaller packs, such as 1 kg or 5 kg bags, catering to household needs.</li>\n \t<li><strong>Custom Packaging:</strong> Tailored packaging solutions based on client specifications, including private labeling and customized bag sizes.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Export Readiness:</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Our glutinous rice adheres to international quality standards, making it an excellent choice for export markets.</li>\n \t<li>Packaging and labeling can be customized to comply with specific import regulations and market preferences of various countries.</li>\n</ul>",
